title: The Fairy Ring
creator: Kate Douglas Wiggin
description: LibriVox recording of The Fairy Ring, edited by Kate Douglas Wiggin and Nora Archibald Smith. The Fairy Ring, originally published in 1910, is a collection of 63 fairy tales from around the globe. It includes such well-known favorites as "History of Jack the Giant-Killer", "The Frog Prince","Rumpel-stilts-ken", and "Snow-white and Rose-red", among many others. Children of all ages will enjoy these stories. (Summary by Paul Williams) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: Fairy tales; children; fantasy; Librivox; audiobook
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
